<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="258" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d258">
                        <head>258. Memorandum from <persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Kaysen</persName> to
                            Gen. <persName corresp="#p_TMD_1">Taylor</persName>, January 23<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d258fn1">Relays President’s interest in
                                having <persName corresp="#p_TMD_1">Taylor</persName> talk with
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName>. No
                                classification marking. 1 p. Kennedy Library, National Security
                                Files, Departments and Agencies Series, <gloss target="#t_DOD_1">DOD</gloss> 1/62–3/62.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline><date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian" when="1962-01-23">January 23,
                                1962</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d258-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d258-1"/>
                        <list type="subject">
                            <head>SUBJECT</head>
                            <item>Ltr to SecDef 1/22/62 (S)</item>
                        </list>
                        <p>The President sent your memorandum to the Secretary and also called him.
                            Judging from my side of the conversation, the Secretary has shown no
                            great increase in his receptivity to this idea. The President indicated
                            he would like <persName corresp="#p_MRS_1">McNamara</persName> to talk
                            to you and <persName corresp="#p_BDE_1">Bell</persName>. I am sending a
                            copy of your memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_BDE_1">Bell</persName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed corresp="#p_KC_1"><persName corresp="#p_KC_1">Carl
                                    Kaysen</persName></signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>